                                <p class="card-text text-body-tertiary">
                                    Stitch_direction_None: This variable indicates whether mummies were marked with no textiles or no stitch direction of textiles found,
                                    and is represented by a value of 1. In contrast, mummies where stitch direction was found are marked as 1 in a different category.
                                </p>
                                <p class="card-text text-body-tertiary">
                                    Count: This variable refers to yarn manipulation and is a numeric variable. Records marked with 0 indicate cases where no yarn
                                    was found or it was unknown. Notably, Count was the variable with the highest value used in creating Principal Component 1,
                                    which was used to differentiate clusters.
                                </p>
                                <p class="card-text text-body-tertiary">
                                    Textile_function_value_None: This is a categorical variable with possible values such as fragmentary, ribbon, blanket/shroud,
                                    tunic, and other. A value closer to 1 indicates that no textile function was assigned to the textiles found or none were found.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
